{
  "texts": [
    "SSG [53] integrates the MOND approach from DPG [86] and closely follows the steps of NSG [54] and DPG [86] in index building from a foundational graph.",
    "Instead of performing a search for each node to acquire candidates, SSG [53] employs a breadth-first search on each node to assemble candidate neighbors through local expansion on a base graph (EFANNA).",
    "When the maximum size for the candidate neighbors is achieved, SSG reduces the neighbors in the list by enforcing the MOND diversification strategy, pruning the candidate nodes forming an angle smaller than a userdefined parameter 𝜃 with the already existing neighbors of the concerned node.",
    "After iteratively applying this method to all nodes, SSG [53] enhances connectivity by constructing multiple DFS trees from various random points, in contrast to NSG's [54] singular DFS approach.",
    "Hierarchical Clustering-based Nearest Neighbor Graph (HCNNG) [102] was inspired by SPTAG."
  ]
}